A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended I was just working from home, actually editing Addicted.
If only this damn file could open. (OneDrive is truly garbage.)
*The hacker's voice* I've entered.
He started drilling, the sound was incredibly loud. Great.
Turn the air purifier to the highest setting; it feels a bit too aggressive, but I did detect a scent of sawdust, so this isn't entirely unreasonable. Besides, he even opposes wearing masks. And I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can only do that after he leaves.
Good news is, Chapter Four is finally edited!
Chapter Five is incredibly long and super anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's so thrilling.
Searching and replacing...➡️Ellipsis, there are 54 in this chapter😅
But I still insist on this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally charged.
The floor repairman is using a vacuum cleaner to clean up, hoping it means he's about to finish.
He went out (sounds like) cutting something. I sneaked a peek at the progress. There's still a lot to do :(|
Chapter five has seven pages left. It's still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in pretty good shape, mainly involving adjustments in formatting, as well as some minor changes to active voice and conciseness. But I really need a break and a cup of tea, and that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Hopefully, this is a good sign.
The floor repairman for the kitchen is gone!
He told me he quoted the price for the whole floor repair, but the landlord is too tight and only agrees to pay for the area by the door that was already rotten. It feels much better.
I was having tea in the garden while the air purifier in the kitchen worked hard to purify the room's air!
